  "texts": [
    "Algorithm 3 RGD for PoLAR-parameterized (25) Require: Learning rates η, γ; sample X 0 uniformly from St(m, r). for t = 0,.",
    ", T -1 do Find Θ t via (26a) Obtain Riemannian gradient G t using (26b) Update X t+1 with (26c) end for This section extends our theoretical results to symmetric matrix factorization problems.",
    "While slightly deviating from the LoRA application, we still include these results because we believe the improvement of the ϵ and κ dependence is important in its own right.",
    "Let B ∈ R m×m be a symmetric positive semi-definite matrix with rank(B) = r B.",
    "Its compact SVD is given by B = UΣU ⊤, where U ∈ R m×r B and Σ ∈ R r B ×r B."
  ]
}